'''Dr. Vivek Lall''', a world renowned aerospace and defence leader now at [[Lockheed Martin]], has held various key positions with his last stint as Chief Executive of Strategic Development at General Atomics and prior to that CEO and President of Reliance New Ventures [[Reliance Industries Limited]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Mehdudia|first=Sujay|title=Vivek Lall to head US India general aviation working group|url=http://www.thehindu.com/business/Industry/vivek-lall-to-head-us-india-general-aviation-working-group/article4901944.ece|accessdate=25 April 2014|newspaper=[[The Hindu]]|date=10 July 2013}}</ref> Dr. Lall was heading the Boeing (Defence and Space) operations in India from 2007 till April 2011.  Dr. Lall previously worked for the US-based global defense and nuclear giant [[General Atomics]] as the global Chief Executive for international Commercial Strategic Development for General Atomics.<ref>[http://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/aerospace-expert-vivek-lall-quits-ril-to-join-general-atomics-114082601113_1.html]</ref> He has been also recognized as one of the world's top scientists of the twentieth century by Cambridge.<ref>[http://www.indiastrategic.in/topstories3496_Dr_Vivek_Lall_joins_General_Atomics.htm]</ref><ref>[http://securingasia.com/Speakers-Bios.aspx?=107]</ref>
General Atomics is best known for manufacturing one of the most important tools in modern warfare: the Predator, an unmanned spy plane used by the US in many global engagements. As Chief Executive he had US and international responsibilities of strategic development of systems like EMALS. Electromagnetic Aircraft Launch System (EMALS) is a complete launch system designed to replace the existing steam catapult currently being used on U.S. Navy aircraft carriers. EMALS is being considered by the Indian Navy for its forthcoming aircraft carrier.<ref>[http://www.stratpost.com/vivek-lall-quits-reliance-for-general-atomics]</ref><ref>[http://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/aerospace-expert-vivek-lall-quits-ril-to-join-general-atomics-114082601113_1.html]</ref>

He was also affiliated with the United Nations in New York to advise on Broadband and Cyber Security issues for challenges within the global community and provide services that will help address them.<ref>{{cite news|title=Indian cyber security whiz Vivek Lall appointed special advisor to UN|url=http://www.financialexpress.com/news/indian-cyber-security-whiz-vivek-lall-appointed-special-advisor-to-un/1222287|accessdate=25 April 2014|newspaper=[[The Financial Express (India)|The Financial Express]]|date=1 February 2014|agency=[[Press Trust of India]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Vivek Lall to drive UN policy on cyber security|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/world-news/vivek-lall-to-drive-un-policy-on-cyber-security/article1-1178933.aspx|accessdate=25 April 2014|newspaper=[[Hindustan Times]]|date=31 January 2014}}</ref>

==Early life==
Vivek was born on 5 March 1969 in Jakarta, Indonesia.<ref>{{cite news|last=NP|first=Ullekh|title=Ex-Boeing employee Vivek Lall: Meet Mukesh Ambani's Reliance Industries' new soldier|url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2011-05-01/news/29491231_1_vivek-lall-defence-business-boeing|accessdate=25 April 2014|newspaper=[[The Economic Times|Economic Times]]|date=1 May 2011}}</ref> Dr. Lall began his technical education at Canada’s Carleton University and earned his bachelor's degree in Mechanical Engineering. He was also instrumental in conducting research on single-engine blades for Canada’s National Aeronautical Establishment. Vivek completed his Aeronautical Engineering master's degree from [[Embry-Riddle Aeronautical University]] in Florida.<ref>{{cite news|last=Shukla|first=Tarun|title=Ex-Boeing executive Vivek Lall may join Reliance Industries|url=http://www.livemint.com/Companies/vMHkwCDt0bnkJthX5gQohO/ExBoeing-executive-Vivek-Lall-may-join-Reliance-Industries.html|accessdate=25 April 2014|newspaper=[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]]|author2=Malik Aman}}</ref> He also has done his PhD in Aerospace and an MBA from US.  He then worked with NASA Ames Research Center where he was part of a project undertaking research work. With a fellowship from NASA, he finished his PhD in aerospace engineering at [[Wichita State University]], Kansas.<ref>{{cite news|last=NP|first=Ullekh|title=Ex-Boeing employee Vivek Lall: Meet Mukesh Ambani's Reliance Industries' new soldier|url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2011-05-01/news/29491231_1_vivek-lall-defence-business-boeing|accessdate=25 April 2014|newspaper=[[The Economic Times|Economic Times]]|date=1 May 2011}}</ref>

==Career==
During his tenure in defense company Raytheon, he worked on the Joint Primary Aircraft Training System (JPATS) Beechcraft T-6 Texan II. He also worked on various disciplines at the NASA Ames Research Center.<ref>[http://www.stratpost.com/vivek-lall-leading-new-ril-tech-venture]</ref> In 1996, Vivek joined The Boeing Company as an aerospace engineer and working on computational fluid dynamics and air elasticity and loads and dynamics for the 757-300 and 777 aircraft. He moved from engineering to management and later.In 2003, Boeing moved Vivek to Delhi, India, as managing director of Boeing Commercial Airplanes.<ref>{{cite news|title=Boeing bullish on Indian defense market|url=http://www.ndtv.com/video/player/big-fish/boeing-bullish-on-indian-defense-market/98672|accessdate=25 April 2014|newspaper=[[NDTV]]|date=19 August 2009}}</ref> During his tenure, Boeing secured $25 billion worth of commercial aircraft business in India. In May 2007, Vivek was appointed as Vice-President and Country Head for India, Boeing Defense Space & Security.<ref>{{cite news|title=Company Overview of Boeing International Corporation India Private Limited|url=http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=108707808&privcapId=33230421&previousCapId=33230421&previousTitle=Boeing%20International%20Corporation%20India%20Private%20Limited|accessdate=25 April 2014|newspaper=[[Bloomberg Businessweek]]}}</ref> Under his leadership, Boeing concluded the US-India defence deals for C17 strategic lift, P-8I Anti-submarine warfare aircraft and Harpoon Missiles.<ref>{{cite news|title=Boeing in Pact With Hindustan Aeronautics To Buy P-8I Plane Doors|url=http://m.foxbusiness.com/quickPage.html?page=19453&content=33196616&pageNum=-1|accessdate=25 April 2014|newspaper=[[Fox Business Network]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Boeing gets equipment from BEL for Indian Navy aircraft|url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/69045/boeing-gets-equipment-bel-indian.html|accessdate=25 April 2014|newspaper=[[Deccan Herald]]|date=12 May|agency=[[Indo-Asian News Service]]}}</ref> Vivek has previously worked with another defence company, Raytheon.<ref>{{cite news|last=Mohan|first=Man|title=RIL bags strategic military aviation tie-up with Boeing US aerospace major to source 30% of its components from Reliance|url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2013/20130523/main6.htm|accessdate=25 April 2014|newspaper=[[The Tribune (Chandigarh)|The Tribune]]|date=23 May 2013}}</ref> At Reliance, Vivek undertakes production of aircraft, unmanned aerial systems, onboard equipment and various defence equipment in collaboration with foreign partners.<ref>{{cite news|last=Chauhan|first=RS|title=Reliance-backed consortium bags Rs 1000 cr deal to install CCTVs in Mumbai|url=http://www.rediff.com/news/report/reliance-firm-bags-rs-1000-cr-deal-to-install-cctvs-in-mumbai/20120709.htm|accessdate=25 April 2014|newspaper=[[Rediff.com]]|date=10 July 2012}}</ref>

On January 2, 2018 [[Lockheed Martin]] announced the appointment of Vivek as vice president, Aeronautics Strategy and Business Development.<ref>http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/companies/aerospace-expert-vivek-lall-joins-lockheed-martin/article10009219.ece</ref>

==Associations==
* Vivek was appointed as Chairman of the Indo-US Strategic Dialogue by the Indo-American Chamber of Commerce. In August 2011<ref>{{cite news|title=Indian cyber security whiz Vivek Lall appointed special advisor to UN|url=http://www.financialexpress.com/news/indian-cyber-security-whiz-vivek-lall-appointed-special-advisor-to-un/1222287|accessdate=25 April 2014|newspaper=[[The Financial Express (India)|The Financial Express]]|date=1 February 2014|agency=[[Press Trust of India]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Mehdudia|first=Sujay|title=Vivek Lall to head US India general aviation working group|url=http://www.thehindu.com/business/Industry/vivek-lall-to-head-us-india-general-aviation-working-group/article4901944.ece|accessdate=25 April 2014|newspaper=[[The Hindu]]|date=4 October 2013}}</ref> 
* Vivek was appointed as Distinguished Fellow at India's think tank Observer Research Foundation.<ref>{{cite news|last=Mehdudia|first=Sujay|title=Towards cyber defence|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/towards-cyber-defence/article4976036.ece|accessdate=25 April 2014|newspaper=[[The Hindu]]|date=1 August 2013}}</ref>  
* He also served as Chairman of the Defense Committee of The Association of Chambers of Commerce and Industry of India (ASSOCHAM)<ref>{{cite news|last=Mehdudia|first=Sujay|title=Expert recommends enhanced focus on cyber security|url=http://www.thehindu.com/business/Industry/expert-recommends-enhanced-focus-on-cyber-security/article5497675.ece|accessdate=25 April 2014|newspaper=[[The Hindu]]|date=24 December 2013}}</ref>

